# Deploy new VM on Proxmox

1. Select your ISO file  
2. Upload it to the **right disk** (“ISO-H” is preferred but you can choose “local (pve)”). It already has some (Win SRV, Ubuntu Desktop, Ubuntu SRV, Kali Linux).  
   ![][image1]   
3. Go to “ISO Images”  
4. Upload your ISO file using the **upload button** or “***download from url***” which is using the lab bandwidth.  
5. Paste your link and click on “Download”   
   ![][image2]  
   1. For the Upload method, click on “Select File” to **select it in your file system**. You can add a hash algorithm to have an integrity check.  
      ![][image3]  
6. Once it is done, go to “Create VM” on the bottom right of the page  
   ![][image4]  
7. Add a name to the virtual machine (it can be edited later)  
   ![][image5]  
8. Select the disk where is located the ISO file   
   ![][image6]  
9. Then, select your OS. A **Kernel is automatically selected** but you can change it if needed.  
   ![][image7]  
10. On the system page, click on “Qemu Agent”   
    ![][image8]  
11. Select the storage disk you want (**Use it in the order it appears** if it has the right capacity for your project) and select the disk size.  
    ![][image9]  
12. Select the numbers of sockets/cores you want to add for the CPU, and the type of it (qemu, intel, amd, …)  
    ![][image10]  
13. Select the memory (RAM) size  
    ![][image11]  
14. Update your network settings if needed. **Bridge is default mode** so your VM will be exposed on the local network and have **its own IP address** (192.168.1.0/24)

![][image12]

15. Review and **click on finish**  
    ![][image13]
